Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer in overtime as the Boston Celtics rallied to beat the Toronto Raptors 126-123 on Saturday night.
Neemias Queta blocked RJ Barrett's driving layup attempt, giving the ball back to the Celtics with 20.2 seconds remaining.
Post-Match Reflections: The Celtics improved to 11-3 and avoided losing for the third time at TD Garden this season.
The Raptors entered with Scottie Barnes (orbital fracture) and Bruce Brown (right knee) on the mend.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Raptors outscored the Celtics 76-42 in the paint.
Bruno Fernando was helped off the court in the second quarter after landing awkwardly on a teammate's foot while pulling down a rebound.
Others: Jayson Tatum finished with 24 points and 11 rebounds.
Al Horford and Derrick White scored 18 points apiece.
Toronto has lost seven straight and failed to register its first road win of the season.
